race.comment: MAID OF MOOLAH (10) talented mare who was scratched at the barrier on November 4, after becoming fractious in the gates at Randwick. Since fitted with a 740m trial at Randwick and assess on the sharp win at Hawkesbury last start. Capable of testing these at this level. DANCES WITH HOOVES (6) racing in good order over the shorter trips and this looks a target race with her excellent record here. Key jockey change and can finish over the top of these. RUBI'S SERVE (5) trained locally and had genuine excuses second-up, when slow into stride and covered ground for a poor eighth over 1300m at Randwick. Gets a better set-up for this with Berry taking the reins. IT'S A WONDER (7) relished the heavy going when a dominant winner over the 1400m at Rosehill second-up. Undefeated here and can go on with it now.
